name: glucosamine-6-phosphate deaminase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
comment: The enzyme uses ring opening and isomerization of the aldose-ketose type to convert the -CH(-NH2)-CH=O group of glucosamine 6-phosphate into -C(=NH)-CH2-OH, forming 2-deoxy-2-imino-D-arabino-hexitol, which then hydrolyses to yield fructose 6-phosphate and ammonia. N-Acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate, which is not broken down, activates the enzyme.

pathways.ec00520: Amino sugar and nucleotide sugar metabolism
